{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Portfolio Cloud*. Using *JIRA Portfolio Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JPOSERVER-1347].
  {panel}

Currently my organisation uses a custom field to assign teams to issues in JIRA. With Portfolio's existing functionality we will need to both assign a value to the custom field in JIRA (to allow filtering) and assign and manage the team in Portfolio.

We'd really like to replace the custom field with the Portfolio field.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Portfolio Cloud*. Using *JIRA Portfolio Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JPOSERVER-1828].
  {panel}

We are trying to leverage the team member availability feature to record time offs, sick days etc.  Currently, all team members have to individually enter any public holidays happening in their country by manually adding them.  It would be a great feature if the system does that automatically based on the GEO or some other metadata that we can enter once.

It would also be nice if the team member can save a link on their browser that would take them right to their vacation settings.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Portfolio Cloud*. Using *JIRA Portfolio Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JPOSERVER-1377].
  {panel}

Use case: To have a global availability and to switch team members between different teams. So I need to reduce the availability for a certain period for a particular period

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Portfolio Cloud*. Using *JIRA Portfolio Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JPOSERVER-1637].
  {panel}

Stream colours could be defined in Classic plans so that you could visualise versions from multiple projects grouped together.

Add colour coding or CPR releases to quickly see how different projects overlap so that you can easily make changes.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Portfolio Cloud*. Using *JIRA Portfolio Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JPOSERVER-1567].
  {panel}

In the issues I can not read nothing about them.
If I have something like a zoom, or put a date range in order to view less information, but with more details

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Portfolio Cloud*. Using *JIRA Portfolio Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JPOSERVER-1396].
  {panel}

We would like the ability to add and roll up (where values are numeric) additional columns in the scope section including custom and calculated/scripted custom fields. 

Multiple saved views for the scope section would also be useful if additional columns are allowed (e.g. 2-3 different options with different columns available for each, rather than users needing to add and remove columns to change views)

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Portfolio Cloud*. Using *JIRA Portfolio Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JPOSERVER-1432].
  {panel}

As I try out Portfolio I've created five separate Portfolios. Some are Live, some are variations of the earlier versions. Each time I have to recreate the teams, skills, themes, etc. 

Being able to copy/dupe/clone, then modify from that would be a huge timesaver and probably encourage more experimentation and/or creative use of the tool.

Consistency is hard to maintain when you're building all that stuff from scratch on 18 projects.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Portfolio Cloud*. Using *JIRA Portfolio Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JPOSERVER-1324].
  {panel}

In Live Plans, it would be useful if releases from different projects could grouped together and managed as one.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Portfolio Cloud*. Using *JIRA Portfolio Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JPOSERVER-1603].
  {panel}

Allow multiple select of columns and bulk update for the Releases, Teams, and Themes Columns. Also, drop down selection should be alphabetical order to improve efficiency.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Portfolio Cloud*. Using *JIRA Portfolio Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JPOSERVER-1623].
  {panel}

Portfolio for JIRA allows you to visualise dependencies between issues in the schedule view, but it will only ever show you the blocking item/s and the blocked item/s for a given issue.
It would be nice to have the option to view the _whole dependency chain_ when clicking on an item, perhaps with the immediately preceding and following dependencies highlighted in a different shade to the rest of the dependency chain.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Portfolio Cloud*. Using *JIRA Portfolio Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JPOSERVER-1848].
  {panel}

User can set "Due Date" for epic and stories.

Currently "Target end" is only used in Portofolio Plan.

If we can sync Due Date and Target end, it would be helpful for managing target schedule.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Portfolio Cloud*. Using *JIRA Portfolio Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JPOSERVER-1260].
  {panel}

As a Project Manager I want to see the Epic Due Date in JIRA Portfolio so that I can quickly see how project deadlines (fixed) may be impacted by the iterative development work within a given release.

Business Context: We work on the development with Scrum, but many projects are traditionally (waterfall) determined and we do our best to meet those deadlines.  As a result, it would be extremely useful to simply add the Epic Due Date to JIRA Portfolio so that we could combine those very different worlds in one place.  It would also help a lot of our PMs get off MS Project and actually use JIRA Portfolio!

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Portfolio Cloud*. Using *JIRA Portfolio Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JPOSERVER-1422].
  {panel}

Capacity views are a critical piece of planning and reporting. The view available in standard plans provided a valuable view, and should be brought forward to Live Plans.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Portfolio Cloud*. Using *JIRA Portfolio Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JPOSERVER-1660].
  {panel}

Updates in portfolio are too slow. Is there any way to improve speed?

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Portfolio Cloud*. Using *JIRA Portfolio Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JPOSERVER-1686].
  {panel}

This is a request to have a pre-defined list of groupers (Themes or Components) that carry across JIRA and Portfolio without dual documentation. And whatever is chosen, it should be allowed to be incorporated into hierarchy in Portfolio and as both a filter and column option in Portfolio.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Portfolio Cloud*. Using *JIRA Portfolio Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JPOSERVER-525].
  {panel}

The Theme field currently only lives in the JIRA Portfolio context and doesn't transfer to the linked JIRA issue. It would be really useful for this field to be transferred to the JIRA issue so that it can be used in filters throughout the system, rather than just being limited to the Portfolio view.

A natural progression would be to add Theme filter to the JIRA Agile planning view.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Portfolio Cloud*. Using *JIRA Portfolio Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JPOSERVER-1743].
  {panel}

While using portfolio, we found that many updates that involve adding initiatives, themes, etc. do not necessarily add more information for individual team members who may be watching (or original reporters) on a story. 

Similar to JIRA's bulk action "send email updates" checkbox it would be great to have quieter updates to tickets, as it can generate hundreds or more emails in a single portfolio publish.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Portfolio Cloud*. Using *JIRA Portfolio Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JPOSERVER-1216].
  {panel}

As a user I want to change the colour of backlog items e.g. initiatives to red, epics to blue, and user stories to green.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Portfolio Cloud*. Using *JIRA Portfolio Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JPOSERVER-1398].
  {panel}

When the roadmap view is broken down to sprints and stages, it would be good if clicking the name of the sprint gave you additional information (like start and end dates, summary info on how much work is open/in progress/done etc), or linked to view the sprint in JIRA Agile (when the sprint exists in JIRA Agile)

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Portfolio Cloud*. Using *JIRA Portfolio Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JPOSERVER-1650].
  {panel}

I have noticed that when you select a Theme at the Epic level, the epic linked stories are also updated in Portfolio. However, any subsequent stories added to the Epic must have the Theme manually updated in Portfolio. It would be great if the Theme on newly created stories inherit the Epic's Theme too.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Portfolio Cloud*. Using *JIRA Portfolio Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JPOSERVER-1741].
  {panel}

Now it's possible to define Maximum assignees per story globally per plan. It would be nice to be able to define maximum assignees per story.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Portfolio Cloud*. Using *JIRA Portfolio Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JPOSERVER-1636].
  {panel}

Go to a plan, select Reports and switch report to Schedule, then change the Schedule settings to show Projects. The Project Key on the left side seems to only show the first 2/3 characters, with no hover over information, nor can the Project Key section be resized to make it readable.
Please see attached screenshots.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Portfolio Cloud*. Using *JIRA Portfolio Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JPOSERVER-1215].
  {panel}

As a user I want to determine the velocity/capacity of the teams for each sprint so that I can plan the release based on actual velocity per sprint.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Portfolio Cloud*. Using *JIRA Portfolio Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JPOSERVER-1397].
  {panel}

It would be great to be able to adjust the order of columns in the scope view

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Portfolio Cloud*. Using *JIRA Portfolio Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JPOSERVER-1693].
  {panel}

However, I want the Estimates column – which syncs with Story Point values on an issue – to remain as hours. 

For example, I have an issue that is 5 SPs and in J4P we convert SPs to hours 1:1. In the aggregated Estimates column, it shows 5 (hours). If I expand the estimate fields, I'd like to be able to say this story requires 10% ops and 90% java, for example. Instead of having to manually type hours, which thens blows out the synced estimate.

(It would also be useful if we could say what skills are needed for an individual issue as JPO-1688 would provide)

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Portfolio Cloud*. Using *JIRA Portfolio Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JPOSERVER-1230].
  {panel}

As a user I want to have expand/collapse all button for the backlog items so that I can expand/collapse all

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Portfolio Cloud*. Using *JIRA Portfolio Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JPOSERVER-1400].
  {panel}

Clicking an issue in the scope section and having an issue detail panel (like the issue navigator, and JIRA service desk) would be great. Even a configurable panel like JIRA Agile would be helpful.

At the moment if I want to see more information about an item I need to switch context from the Portfolio plan as the issue key links to the full JIRA view of an issue.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Portfolio Cloud*. Using *JIRA Portfolio Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JPOSERVER-1597].
  {panel}

The scope selection in the plan creation wizard doesn't show completed issues even though they are also pulled into the plan.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Portfolio Cloud*. Using *JIRA Portfolio Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JPOSERVER-1365].
  {panel}

Live plans don't seem to show original estimates anymore. Currently need to continually adjust estimates based on history.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Portfolio Cloud*. Using *JIRA Portfolio Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JPOSERVER-1665].
  {panel}

If there is a dependency between two stories you can see there is a dependency in the schedule view when viewing the epic level, but on clicking the epic the detail panel says there is no dependency. 

While technically this is true for the epic, it's very confusing for users as they are not able to see which issues actually have dependencies without going through each of the stories.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Portfolio Cloud*. Using *JIRA Portfolio Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JPOSERVER-1708].
  {panel}

Hi,

In Portfolio for JIRA I can set estimates for each stage separatly. But when developer logs work in Jira, it reduces overall estimates for issue. Estimates for stages recalculated automaticaly depending on persantage.

It would be much better if developer could add type of work when he logs work. And estimates for concrete stage of work should be reduced in Portfolio.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Portfolio Cloud*. Using *JIRA Portfolio Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JPOSERVER-1300].
  {panel}

I want to be able to add dependencies directly in the Scope view of a Live plan (as provided in the static plans).

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Portfolio Cloud*. Using *JIRA Portfolio Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JPOSERVER-1812].
  {panel}

The field team (from JIRA Portfolio) should keep the team name instead of the team id when saved as a filter.

If you create a JQL search: Team = Red and save it as a filter, it will save Team = 1 (the team ID on this example).

It will cause extra work every time that you open a filter with a team to discover to which team that ID belongs.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Portfolio Cloud*. Using *JIRA Portfolio Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JPOSERVER-1659].
  {panel}

I may be missing something, but currently if I sort by the progress column in the Portfolio scope section, there doesn't seem to be a way to revert back to sorting on rank other than removing and re-adding the column I've sorted on.

It would be great if there was some obvious way to revert back to sorting on rank, this is causing confusion for users as they can no longer reprioritise their issues and it's not clear why.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Portfolio Cloud*. Using *JIRA Portfolio Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JPOSERVER-1378].
  {panel}

Want to be able to add hierarchy levels that aren't mapped to issue types and that aren't pushed to JIRA/Agile boards.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Portfolio Cloud*. Using *JIRA Portfolio Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JPOSERVER-1591].
  {panel}

We would like to see the projected dates from the Portfolio plans (Start date, End date) visible on the issues when viewing them directly in JIRA.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Portfolio Cloud*. Using *JIRA Portfolio Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JPOSERVER-1745].
  {panel}

Stories that have an epic link but where the epic is not included in a portfolio plan display as issues without epics, this is causing confusion for some of our teams (we're aware the behavior is the same as JIRA Agile). 

It would be good to have some indication on these issues that they belong to an epic but it is not included in the plan.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Portfolio Cloud*. Using *JIRA Portfolio Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JPOSERVER-1863].
  {panel}

Portfolio Themes are plan-specific at the moment. That is, when you assign _Issue A_ to _Theme A_ in _Plan A_ and look at _Issue A_ in _Plan B_, _Theme A_ does not show up on the issue. It would be great to have a way of sharing themes between plans, similar to how teams and skills can be shared.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Portfolio Cloud*. Using *JIRA Portfolio Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JPOSERVER-1689].
  {panel}

I just realized that everyone shares the same view of draft edits!!!

What?  That means that you can't tinker with a plan without changing everyone's view of the plan.

I suggest that draft edits need to be scoped to an individual.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Portfolio Cloud*. Using *JIRA Portfolio Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JPOSERVER-1330].
  {panel}

It would be immensely useful to my organization if we could export our Project Template (that we created) in to a .CSV so that we can distribute it to our PM's to use for Formatting in the format in which we want to run projects through Jira. Is this possible without exporting the entire backup?? Haven't bee nable to find the documentation on it.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Portfolio Cloud*. Using *JIRA Portfolio Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JPOSERVER-1577].
  {panel}

Not all projects have the same skills/stages % ratio. Some projects require more design, development etc. It would be useful to define a different mix of skills/stages % for individual issue sources for distributing estimates and calculating the schedule.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Portfolio Cloud*. Using *JIRA Portfolio Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JPOSERVER-1880].
  {panel}

Currently, the documentation doesn't explicitly specify the limit for number of issues in the plan. This knowledge can be found in:
* https://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JPO-1671
* https://answers.atlassian.com/questions/39140034/how-to-confirmlimit-the-number-of-issues-into-portfolio

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Portfolio Cloud*. Using *JIRA Portfolio Server*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JPOSERVER-497].
  {panel}

Under plan in JIRA Portfolio, at the moment, user does not have the option to re-arrange/re-order the column. It would be great to have this feature.
